text: Kulakovka () is a rural locality (a selo) in Tryokhprotoksky Selsoviet, Privolzhsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 1,365 as of 2010. There are 20 streets. == Geography == It is located 5 km WSW from Nachalovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Privolzhsky District, Astrakhan Oblast
title: Kulakovka
